HEADWORD: Deglutition
<hw>Deg`lu*ti"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deglutire</ets> to swallow down; <ets>de-</ets> +
<ets>glutire</ets> to swallow: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧glutition</ets>. See
<er>Glut</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of swallowing food; the
power of swallowing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The muscles employed in the act of <qex>deglutition</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
